Synchronize the persistent entities with the underlying database. This should not need to be called by users, as it will be automatically performed when changes are made via this factory. The synchronization will affect all entities sharing the underlying entity manager and not just those managed by this factory.

This scale describes the situation when you have a set of strings as the sets of objects in question. Accepts any strings or terms.

A scale whose elements consist of a choice from a list of pre-defined items. The items are assumed to be mutually exclusive.
Abstract class for numeric scales.
Numeric scales will also have minimum and maximum values that can be specified, with the specific type of minimum or maximum determined by the subclasses.
TODO: There may be a way to implement this as a generic class where the min and max are parameters, but it isn't clear how that interacts with the persistent store's need to know the type of the stored values. For now, therefore it is implemented with replication of the functions and code in the subclasses.
